main event: A civilian observed an elongated, illuminated object moving silently across the sky over San Francisco on September 2, 1968.
interesting points: The object appeared in the southwestern horizon and was partially obscured by clouds., It had a pale white glow and emitted no visible light sources., The object moved in a straight line at a high rate of speed., The observation lasted several seconds before the object disappeared behind the horizon., The report indicates there was insufficient data for evaluation.
